To fully complete the tic-tac-toe game, we must add logic to check for wins in columns and diagonals. Let me provide a continuation of the `checkForWin` function to include these checks:

```javascript
function checkForWin(playerClass) {
  const SIZE = 4;
  const board = document.querySelectorAll('.tic-tac-toe-row');

  // Check rows and columns
  for (let i = 0; i < SIZE; i++) {
    let rowWin = true;
    let colWin = true;

    for (let j = 0; j < SIZE; j++) {
      // Check the row
      if (!board[i].children[j].classList.contains(playerClass)) {
        rowWin = false;
      }
      // Check the column
      if (!board[j].children[i].classList.contains(playerClass)) {
        colWin = false;
      }
    }

    if (rowWin || colWin) {
      return true;
    }
  }

  // Check diagonals
  let diag1Win = true;
  let diag2Win = true;
  for (let i = 0; i < SIZE; i++) {
    // Check the leading diagonal (top-left to bottom-right)
    if (!board[i].children[i].classList.contains(playerClass)) {
      diag1Win = false;
    }
    // Check the anti-diagonal (top-right to bottom-left)
    if (!board[i].children[SIZE - 1 - i].classList.contains(playerClass)) {
      diag2Win = false;
    }
  }

  if (diag1Win || diag2Win) {
    return true;
  }

  return false; // No win found
}
```

With this complete `checkForWin` function, our JavaScript code can now correctly identify a winner for a 4x4 tic-tac-toe game by checking all rows, columns, and diagonals for any winning patterns.

